HEADWORD: Cephalothorax
<hw>Ceph`a*lo*tho"rax</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Cephalo-</ets> + <ets>thorax</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The anterior portion of any one of the Arachnida and higher
Crustacea, consisting of the united head and thorax.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

